                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 816.48/15</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-15T11:00:00-05:56">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of June 13, 6 p.m. Salvadorean Red Cross has accepted with
                    appropriate expression of appreciation 5,000 dollars; through an amicable
                    arrangement with Government’s commissions, Red Cross will administer funds it
                    accepts with free hand. Even so, more money for the Red Cross and supplementary
                    fund are necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
